<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: SDSU PICKED SEVENTH IN FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego State football team has been picked by to finish seventh in the 
nine-team Western Athletic Conference next season. 
</P>
<P>
Meeting in Sun Valley, Ida., on Sunday, reporters covering the conference 
picked Brigham Young to win the WAC title. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars, who have won 12 conference titles, including 10 in a row from 
1976-85, received 25 first-place votes of the 32 cast by reporters at the 
annual football preview. 
</P>
<P>
Coaches were not polled. 
</P>
<P>
BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego girls' 13-year-old Police Athletic League team earned a berth in 
the third round of the Junior National Basketball Championships in Coral 
Springs, Fla., with a 60-51 victory over Oregon. De Angela Minter led San Diego 
with 14 points, and Jeanie Shadian added 10. San Diego will play North Carolina 
Tuesday in the 40-team national tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
