<TEXT>
<P>
Shrimpers blocking shipping lanes off Texas and Louisiana yielded to traffic 
after the Coast Guard agreed to hear their complaints about regulations 
intended to protect an endangered species of sea turtle. "If something is not 
done, there'll probably be violence," said Marvin Hickman, a shrimper from 
Tarpon Springs, Fla. At issue is a Commerce Department rule requiring use of 
what the shrimpers say is a cumbersome and costly device to allow sea turtles 
to escape the nets. About 200 shrimp boats had crowded the deep-water channel 
at Galveston, Tex. About 300 others jammed access to the Port of Corpus 
Christi, and smaller ports in both states were blocked. 
