<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 HURT IN FALL FROM CLIFF AT LA JOLLA BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two beachgoers were injured Sunday afternoon after falling 30 feet off a La 
Jolla cliff to the beach below, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Kirk Anderson, 35, and a 35-year-old woman, whose name had not been released 
pending notification of relatives, were walking down a trail on a cliff above 
the south end of Black's Beach about 3 p.m. when they realized the trail was a 
false one, a spokesman for the San Diego lifeguards said. 
</P>
<P>
As they tried to make their way down to the beach, they slipped and fell about 
30 feet to a patch of sand and rocks below, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Anderson suffered a fractured leg in the fall, while the woman received a head 
injury. Both were transported to Scripps Memorial Hospital and listed in stable 
condition Sunday night, a spokeswoman for the hospital said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
