<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SLAIN IN SANTEE NEIGHBORHOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was shot and killed Sunday evening in a Santee neighborhood, and 
sheriff's deputies surrounded the area in an attempt to catch the assailant, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, who had not been identified Sunday night, died from a gunshot wound 
to the chest after being rushed by Life Flight to Sharp Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting took place in the 8800 block of Olive Lane near Mac Cool Lane 
about 6 p.m., a Sheriff's Department spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities surrounded the neighborhood for more than two hours and believed 
the assailant was trapped in the area, but by late Sunday a suspect had not 
been apprehended, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
