<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ALCOTT STICKS WITH 68 AND WINS BY THREE SHOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amy Alcott shot her fourth straight 68 Sunday to win the Boston Five tournament 
at Danvers, Mass., by three strokes with a 16-under-par 272 total -- best score 
this year on the LPGA Tour. 
</P>
<P>
Alcott, who moved to third on the LPGA's all-time earnings list, began the day 
with a two-shot lead over Shirley Furlong. It never dropped below three after 
Alcott birdied the second hole. 
</P>
<P>
Curt Byrum joined his brother as a first-time winner on the PGA Tour this year 
by coming from behind to win the Hardee's tournament at Coal Valley, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
Byrum, whose brother, Tom, won the Kemper Open in June, shot a four-under-par 
66 for a 268 total and capitalized on the collapse of defending champion Blaine 
McCallister to finish one shot ahead of Brian Tennyson and Bill Britton. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce Crampton shot a four-under-par 68 for a one-stroke victory at 205over Jim 
Ferree and Orville Moody in the $500,000 Ameritech Senior Open at Cleveland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
