<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS WIN AMERICAN LEGION TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Carter and Tom Wilson each hit home runs as the Fullerton Angels defeated 
the Fullerton Dodgers, 5-2, Sunday in the championship game of the American 
Legion District 29 baseball tournament at Glover Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Carter hit a solo homer in the third inning, his third home run of the 
tournament. Wilson hit a two-run homer in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Trachsel pitched a five-hitter, striking out seven, for the victory. 
Trachsel won two games and saved another in the tournament. He also had two 
home runs in the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton advances to the Area 5 tournament, which begins Thursday at Upland 
Memorial Park. 
</P>
</TEXT>
