WOMAN HIT BY CARS IS IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pedestrian struck by two cars in South Laguna was identified today by 
hospital officials as Herrisa Pennywell, 26, of Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Pennywell remained in critical condition at Mission Hospital Regional Medical 
Center in Mission Viejo after the accident Sunday on Coast Highway. 
</P>
<P>
She was struck as she attempted to cross the highway about 1:30 p.m. near West 
Street, Laguna Beach police said. After being knocked into the hood and 
windshield of a car driven by a Long Beach man, Pennywell rolled back into the 
roadway and was struck by another motorist driving in a northbound lane. 
</P>
<P>
Both drivers stopped and summoned help. Neither was cited, Police Sgt. Ray 
Lardie said. 
</P>
<P>
Pennywell's identity initially was a mystery because she carried no 
identification. Lardie said her boyfriend provided identification. 
</P>
