HEART, LUNG RECIPIENT, 7, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 7-year-old cystic fibrosis patient who underwent a heart-lung transplant in 
April died early today at Stanford University Hospital of complications of 
surgery, hospital officials said. 
</P>
<P>
David Laird Jr., who suffered from a severe form of the disease since birth, 
died of postoperative infection and pneumonia, a hospital spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, son of Deanna and David Laird Sr. of Ceres, was the youngest patient 
with the disease to have a heart-lung transplant at the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
"David was an exceptional kid. He had a lot of spirit," said hospital spokesman 
Diarmuid McGuire. "He was a fighter. That was one of the reasons he was chosen, 
I think, for this very difficult procedure. His spirit was so strong." 
</P>
