<P>
$3 MILLION FOR 1935 MERCEDES-BENZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONACO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Parisian car dealer paid $3 million for a 1935 Mercedes-Benz roadster at a 
Sotheby's Monaco auction this weekend, a Sotheby's spokesman said today. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the famous auction house said the bid by the unidentified 
dealer set a record for the highest amount paid for any article to auctioned by 
Sotheby's in Monaco. 
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Mercedes 500K Special roadster was judged the most 
beautiful automobile when it was first shown in the 1935 World Automobile Show 
in Berlin. 
