<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
WAYNE COOPER SIGNS WITH BLAZERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PORTLAND, Ore. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Denver Nuggets free agent Wayne Cooper signed a contract with the Portland 
Trail Blazers today. Blazers spokesman John Lashway said the contract was 
signed after the 6-foot-10 center underwent a physical by the Blazers' team 
physician. 
</P>
<P>
Lashway said details of the contract will be announced later. The Rocky 
Mountain News reported in Denver that Cooper was signing a three-year contract 
that NBA sources said would bring him $1.1 million a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
